President Trump welcomed President Abbas to the White House for his first visit to Washington in a while. President Trump expressed his commitment to working with Israel and the Palestinians to reach an agreement for peace, but emphasized that it cannot be imposed by the United States or any other nation. He also highlighted the importance of defeating ISIS and other terrorist groups, and applauded the Palestinian Authority's security coordination with Israel. President Abbas stated that their strategic choice is to bring about peace based on the two-state solution, which would give impetus to the Arab peace initiative and enable the fight against terrorism. Both leaders expressed hope for a historic peace treaty. President Trump acknowledged that the Israeli-Palestinian deal is considered one of the toughest to make, but he is hopeful that progress can be achieved.